insert into ai_tools
  (slug, title, category_slug, category_order, display_order, summary, body_md, founded, url)
values
  ('claude', 'Claude', 'general-assistants', 1, 1, 'Claude is Anthropic''s frontier AI assistant — a family of large language models designed to be helpful, honest and broadly capable, but with a particular reputation for the qualities that matter in business work: tone, nuance, judgement and the ability to handle long, messy…', $md$Claude is Anthropic's frontier AI assistant — a family of large language models designed to be helpful, honest and broadly capable, but with a particular reputation for the qualities that matter in business work: tone, nuance, judgement and the ability to handle long, messy documents without losing the thread. It is generally considered the strongest model on the market for high-stakes writing, structured reasoning, document analysis and software engineering, and it is the model most often chosen when output quality matters more than raw speed. Claude is accessible through the consumer chat at [Claude.ai](http://Claude.ai), the Claude API for developers, the Claude Code agentic coding CLI, and integrations like Claude in Chrome and Claude in Excel — meaning the same underlying model can sit inside whatever tool the team is already using.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Draft seasonal product descriptions for an entire collection in one go — feed Claude the design brief, materials, gemstone provenance and brand voice guide, and have it produce on-tone copy for site, ads and email.
- **Calo (subscription meal delivery):** Use Claude with long context to ingest a full month of NPS verbatims plus Trustpilot reviews per region (UK / KSA / UAE / Bahrain / Kuwait / Qatar / Oman), and have it cluster issues by theme, severity and region for the weekly leadership review.
- **Agency:** Build a "strategy partner" workflow — paste a client brief, brand guidelines and competitive landscape into a Project, and use Claude to generate positioning territories, messaging frameworks and creative directions that the team then refines.
**Getting started**
1. Go to [claude.ai](http://claude.ai) and sign up (free tier available; Pro for daily power-users; Team / Enterprise for shared Projects and admin controls).
2. Create a *Project* per workstream (e.g. "Calo UK Marketing", "Brand Voice"). Drop in your brand guidelines, past creatives and reference docs as project knowledge.
3. Turn on connectors you actually use (Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Notion, Slack) so Claude can pull live context.
4. For repeated tasks, save prompts as Artifacts or in a Notion "Prompt Library" page.$md$, 'Anthropic, 2021 (San Francisco). Claude first released March 2023.', 'https://www.anthropic.com/claude'),
  ('chatgpt', 'ChatGPT', 'research-writing', 2, 1, 'ChatGPT is OpenAI''s flagship consumer AI product and the application that turned modern AI into a mainstream tool when it launched in November 2022.', $md$ChatGPT is OpenAI's flagship consumer AI product and the application that turned modern AI into a mainstream tool when it launched in November 2022. It is built around the GPT family of models and is now an entire productivity ecosystem rather than a single chatbot — including reasoning models (the o-series) for harder analytical work, GPT-Image for native image generation, voice mode for spoken conversations, code interpreter for sandboxed Python execution, web browsing, and agentic browsing via Operator. On top of that, the Custom GPT marketplace and Projects let teams package up specific instructions, files and tools into reusable assistants for recurring jobs. For most marketers it is the default "general AI" — the one most colleagues will already be using — and its breadth across writing, ideation, image generation and lightweight automation makes it a strong everyday workhorse.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Use a custom GPT trained on the brand's tone-of-voice doc to spin out 30+ Instagram caption variants per drop, then use GPT-Image to mock up campaign visual concepts before briefing the photographer.
- **Calo:** Build a custom GPT loaded with the meal menu, macros, and ingredient lists so the customer-care team can instantly answer "is this dish gluten-free / halal / suitable for gestational diabetes?" type queries in any region.
- **Agency:** Use ChatGPT's deep research mode to produce a 20-page market scan for a new pitch in under an hour — competitive landscape, trends, audience insights — and refine into a deck-ready narrative.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [chatgpt.com](http://chatgpt.com) (Plus £20/mo gives access to o-series reasoning and image / video). Team or Enterprise for SOC 2 + zero data retention.
2. Build a *Custom GPT* per recurring use-case (Brand Voice GPT, Product Description GPT).
3. Use *Projects* to keep linked threads, files and instructions together.
4. Try Operator (agentic web browsing) for tasks like "compare 10 competitor pricing pages and dump into a table".$md$, 'OpenAI, 2015. ChatGPT launched November 2022.', 'https://chatgpt.com'),
  ('perplexity', 'Perplexity', 'research-writing', 2, 2, 'Perplexity is an "answer engine" — instead of returning a list of blue links the way Google does, you ask a question in plain English and it returns a synthesised answer with inline citations to the actual sources, plus suggested follow-up questions to keep the line of enquiry…', $md$Perplexity is an "answer engine" — instead of returning a list of blue links the way Google does, you ask a question in plain English and it returns a synthesised answer with inline citations to the actual sources, plus suggested follow-up questions to keep the line of enquiry going. Under the hood it combines live web search with frontier LLMs (you can choose which one), which makes it materially better than a vanilla ChatGPT for current information, time-sensitive competitive intel, and any work where you need to be able to defend a claim with a real source. The Spaces feature lets teams keep persistent research threads per project or client, and Comet (Perplexity's browser) bakes the same answer engine into normal day-to-day browsing. It has effectively become the modern replacement for "I'll just google it" for serious knowledge workers.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Run weekly "who is winning in lab-grown diamond marketing right now?" scans — Perplexity returns cited articles, recent campaigns and industry analyst takes the team can act on.
- **Calo:** Track GLP-1 / weight-loss meal plan trends across UK and GCC press in real time so the menu team and marketing team are aligned on what's resonating in each market.
- **Agency:** Build a pitch with bulletproof citations — use *Spaces* to keep a research thread per client and let strategists pull verified stats into decks without rabbit-holing in Google.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [perplexity.ai](http://perplexity.ai). Pro (£17/mo) unlocks unlimited Pro searches and frontier models.
2. Use the *Focus* dropdown to scope searches (Academic, Social, YouTube, Reddit).
3. Set up *Spaces* per client / project to keep research siloed.
4. Pin the Comet browser if you want Perplexity baked into your daily browsing.$md$, 'Perplexity AI, 2022 (San Francisco). Founders Aravind Srinivas, Denis Yarats, Johnny Ho and Andy Konwinski.', 'https://www.perplexity.ai'),
  ('gemini', 'Gemini', 'research-writing', 2, 3, 'Gemini is Google DeepMind''s flagship model family and Google''s answer to ChatGPT and Claude — a fully multimodal AI that natively handles text, images, audio, video and code, with one of the largest context windows on the market (up to 1M+ tokens, meaning it can read entire…', $md$Gemini is Google DeepMind's flagship model family and Google's answer to ChatGPT and Claude — a fully multimodal AI that natively handles text, images, audio, video and code, with one of the largest context windows on the market (up to 1M+ tokens, meaning it can read entire books, codebases or quarters of meeting transcripts in a single pass). Its biggest strategic advantage isn't the model itself but the distribution: Gemini is woven into Google Workspace, so it shows up directly inside Docs, Sheets, Gmail, Meet and Slides where most marketing work already happens, and it can pull live context from your Drive, Calendar and inbox without any setup. Standalone, it's available at [gemini.google.com](http://gemini.google.com) with deeper features like Deep Research, custom Gems, and access to Veo for video generation on the higher-tier plans. For teams already on Google's stack, Gemini is often the assistant that gets used the most just by virtue of being one click away.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Drop the entire customer Drive (product photos, lookbooks, past campaign decks) into Gemini and ask it to surface visual themes that have driven the highest engagement, then suggest the next campaign mood.
- **Calo:** Use Gemini in Sheets to parse and clean the weekly UK kitchen output CSVs (orders, wastage, repeats) — natural-language formula building beats writing SUMIFS by hand.
- **Agency:** Use Gemini in Meet to auto-summarise client calls, surface action items, and draft a follow-up email in one click.
**Getting started**
1. Most marketers already have access via Google Workspace — turn on Gemini in admin settings.
2. Try the standalone app at [gemini.google.com](http://gemini.google.com) for the longest-context tasks.
3. Try *Gems* (custom assistants) for repeatable tasks like "weekly social brief writer".
4. AI Pro / Ultra plan unlocks Veo video generation and deep research.$md$, 'Google DeepMind, model launched December 2023 (DeepMind itself founded 2010).', 'https://gemini.google.com'),
  ('notebooklm', 'NotebookLM', 'research-writing', 2, 4, 'NotebookLM is Google''s "grounded research workspace" — a deliberately constrained tool where you upload a set of sources (PDFs, web pages, YouTube videos, Google Docs, Slides, audio files) and the AI then answers questions only from those sources, with inline citations to the…', $md$NotebookLM is Google's "grounded research workspace" — a deliberately constrained tool where you upload a set of sources (PDFs, web pages, YouTube videos, Google Docs, Slides, audio files) and the AI then answers questions only from those sources, with inline citations to the exact paragraph it used. Because it is grounded in your sources, it is much harder for it to hallucinate, which makes it ideal for serious analysis where you can't afford an LLM to make things up. It is best known for its viral Audio Overview feature, which turns any set of sources into a surprisingly listenable podcast-style conversation between two synthetic hosts; teams use this to "listen" to long reports on the commute. There's also Mind Map view, briefing docs, FAQ generation and study guides — but the underlying model is the same: bring your own sources, get cited answers.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Build a notebook of every customer review across Trustpilot, [Reviews.io](http://Reviews.io) and Instagram comments, and ask "what do five-star buyers love that three-star buyers complain about?" — the answer is grounded in the actual reviews with citations.
- **Calo:** Drop in regional unit economics decks, P&L exports and brand tracker reports per region, then use Audio Overview to let the leadership team "listen" to the monthly performance read on their commute.
- **Agency:** For pitches — load every public document about a target client (annual report, press, podcast transcripts, Glassdoor reviews) and interrogate it as a single corpus before the discovery call.
**Getting started**
1. Sign in at [notebooklm.google.com](http://notebooklm.google.com) with a Google account.
2. Create a notebook → add up to 50 sources (300 with Plus).
3. Generate a *Briefing Doc* and *Audio Overview* automatically.
4. Ask follow-up questions in chat — every answer cites the source paragraph.$md$, 'Google Labs, public launch July 2023 (originally "Project Tailwind").', 'https://notebooklm.google.com'),
  ('grammarly', 'Grammarly', 'research-writing', 2, 5, 'Grammarly started in 2009 as a grammar checker for students and has now evolved into a full AI writing assistant that runs across virtually every place you write — the browser, Google Docs, Microsoft Word, Gmail, Outlook, Slack, LinkedIn, Notion and more.', $md$Grammarly started in 2009 as a grammar checker for students and has now evolved into a full AI writing assistant that runs across virtually every place you write — the browser, Google Docs, Microsoft Word, Gmail, Outlook, Slack, LinkedIn, Notion and more. The 2026 version goes far beyond spelling and grammar: it can rewrite for tone, calibrate copy to a target audience, suggest more concise alternatives, generate first drafts, and — most importantly for marketing teams — enforce a defined brand voice and style guide across everything the company writes. The Business and Enterprise tiers let you upload a tone-of-voice doc and a glossary of approved / banned terms, and Grammarly will then nudge writers in real time when they drift off-brand. Used well, it functions as an always-on copy editor sitting quietly behind every team member.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Encode the brand voice ("warm, considered, never salesy") and run every site product description, ad copy and email through Grammarly's brand-tuned check before publishing.
- **Calo:** Standardise tone across customer support replies — every CX agent in every region writes in a single, consistent Calo voice without endless QA loops.
- **Agency:** Lock in client-specific style guides as Grammarly *Style Guides* so junior strategists writing for Brand A vs Brand B can't accidentally use the wrong tone.
**Getting started**
1. Install the browser extension and desktop app from [grammarly.com](http://grammarly.com).
2. Business plan gives you a brand voice / style guide that the whole team writes against.
3. Connect Gmail, Docs, Slack, Notion, etc. — Grammarly works inline.$md$, '2009 by Alex Shevchenko, Max Lytvyn and Dmytro Lider (Kyiv / San Francisco).', 'https://www.grammarly.com'),
  ('notion', 'Notion', 'productivity', 3, 1, 'Notion is the all-in-one workspace tool — a single application that combines docs, wikis, project trackers, kanban boards, calendars, databases and lightweight forms into one connected system.', $md$Notion is the all-in-one workspace tool — a single application that combines docs, wikis, project trackers, kanban boards, calendars, databases and lightweight forms into one connected system. What started as a "Lego for software" pitch in 2016 has become the place where most modern companies' institutional knowledge actually lives: SOPs, OKRs, meeting notes, client briefs, content calendars, vendor lists and product specs, all linked together. The 2026 version layers a serious AI on top of that: Notion AI can write, summarise, translate and reformat inside any doc, and Q&A can answer plain-English questions across your entire workspace and connected apps (Slack, Drive, GitHub, Jira) — turning years of accumulated docs into an actually useful, queryable knowledge base. Increasingly Notion is also a calendar, a meeting-notes app, and a forms tool, eating adjacent SaaS tools as it goes.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Run the entire content calendar — drop, campaign, channel, status, owner, asset link — as a Notion database, with AI-generated weekly status digests for the founders.
- **Calo:** Central wiki for SOPs across kitchens, marketing, customer ops; Notion AI Q&A means a new kitchen manager in Doha can ask "what's the SLA for delivery complaints over 90 minutes?" and get the right answer immediately.
- **Agency:** Build a client portal per account with deliverables, status, decks, contracts and meeting notes — turn it into a single tidy workspace clients can actually log into.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [notion.so](http://notion.so). Use a teamspace per function (Marketing, Ops, Finance).
2. Build databases for the things you measure — calendar, briefs, OKRs, vendors.
3. Turn on Notion AI for in-doc generation and full-workspace Q&A.
4. Connect Slack, Drive, GitHub, Jira so AI Q&A reaches outside Notion too.$md$, '2013 by Ivan Zhao and Simon Last; current product launched 2016.', 'https://www.notion.so'),
  ('otio', 'Otio', 'productivity', 3, 2, 'Otio is an AI-native research workspace built specifically for the kind of work where you need to read and synthesise across many sources — analyst reports, academic papers, long articles, YouTube videos, podcasts, PDFs.', $md$Otio is an AI-native research workspace built specifically for the kind of work where you need to read and synthesise across many sources — analyst reports, academic papers, long articles, YouTube videos, podcasts, PDFs. You upload (or import from Drive, Zotero, Mendeley, Dropbox) and Otio reads everything for you, generates cited summaries, and lets you chat across the entire collection of sources at once with answers that link back to the exact paragraph or video timestamp. The product's distinctive bet is that you should be able to swap models — GPT, Claude, Gemini, Mistral, Perplexity — over the same source set, picking whichever model is best for the current task. It's used by researchers at places like DeepMind and Google, and by marketing strategists, consultants and analysts who want a Notion-style writing experience grounded in their own evidence rather than a chatbot's general training data.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Build a "luxury market trends" notebook of analyst PDFs, McKinsey reports and YouTube interviews; query it weekly to spot shifting consumer signals.
- **Calo:** Drop in nutrition science papers, GLP-1 white papers, and competitor menus to brief the menu development team with cited insight, not vibes.
- **Agency:** Each new pitch starts as an Otio notebook — every public document about the prospect, summarised and queryable in one place.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up free at [otio.ai](http://otio.ai).
2. Upload sources or connect Drive / Zotero / Mendeley.
3. Use *Chat* across all sources, then drop synthesised answers into the AI editor to write up.
4. Switch models per task — Claude Opus for synthesis, fast models for summaries.$md$, '2023.', 'https://otio.ai'),
  ('wispr-flow', 'Wispr Flow', 'productivity', 3, 3, 'Wispr Flow is an AI voice-dictation tool that works system-wide on Mac, Windows and iOS — you hit a hotkey, speak naturally, and clean, formatted, on-context text appears in whatever app you''re in, whether that''s Gmail, Slack, Notion, Cursor or a CRM.', $md$Wispr Flow is an AI voice-dictation tool that works system-wide on Mac, Windows and iOS — you hit a hotkey, speak naturally, and clean, formatted, on-context text appears in whatever app you're in, whether that's Gmail, Slack, Notion, Cursor or a CRM. The thing that makes Wispr different from older dictation tools (Apple Dictation, Dragon, Otter) is that it actively rewrites as it transcribes: it strips out filler words ("um", "you know", "like"), repairs sentence structure, formats lists, applies basic markdown, and matches the tone of the surrounding text. Power users routinely report dictating 70%+ of long documents with little or no editing afterwards. Wispr was founded by two Stanford AI researchers and originally tried to build a silent-speech wearable; they pivoted to the software side and have since raised \$81M to build what they call a "voice OS" — an explicit ambition to replace the keyboard as the primary input device for knowledge work.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** A founder dictates Instagram captions while walking the studio between fittings — Wispr formats them into ready-to-post copy, no thumb-typing.
- **Calo:** Customer ops leaders dictate weekly performance commentary into Notion or Slack rather than typing 1,500-word updates after a long shift.
- **Agency:** Strategists dictate raw stream-of-consciousness brainstorms into a Doc; Wispr structures them into bullet-pointed notes the team can build on.
**Getting started**
1. Download the Mac, Windows or iOS app at [wisprflow.ai](http://wisprflow.ai) (14-day free trial).
2. Set a global hotkey (e.g. fn-fn).
3. Speak in any app — the cleaned text replaces the dictation.
4. Use *Command Mode* to give edits like "make this shorter and more direct".$md$, '2021 by Tanay Kothari and Sahaj Garg (San Francisco). Flow launched late 2024.', 'https://wisprflow.ai'),
  ('manus', 'Manus', 'productivity', 3, 4, 'Manus is one of the most-talked-about general-purpose AI agents of 2025 — a system that takes a goal in plain English ("research the UK ready-meal market and build me a deck", "find and book me a flight under £400 to Lisbon next month") and then autonomously plans, browses…', $md$Manus is one of the most-talked-about general-purpose AI agents of 2025 — a system that takes a goal in plain English ("research the UK ready-meal market and build me a deck", "find and book me a flight under £400 to Lisbon next month") and then autonomously plans, browses, codes, fills spreadsheets and writes documents to complete the task, while showing you exactly what it's doing in a live "Manus Computer" window so you can intervene at any point. It launched in March 2025 from a Singapore-based startup called Butterfly Effect (originally Chinese, of "Monica" fame), got \~2 million people on the waitlist within a week, and was acquired by Meta in December 2025 in a deal reportedly valued at \$2–3B. Despite the acquisition, Manus continues to operate as a standalone product. It is one of the clearest current examples of where general-purpose agentic AI is heading: less "chatbot you talk to" and more "junior analyst you delegate to".
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** "Manus, find every UK lab-grown diamond competitor, list their hero SKUs, prices, ad spend signals and key reviewers, and put it in a spreadsheet." Returns a usable competitive scan with no analyst hours burned.
- **Calo:** Run an autonomous task like "compile a weekly review of every food-delivery story in UK and GCC press and summarise implications for Calo" — landed in inbox each Monday.
- **Agency:** Use Manus to do the boring early prep on every new pitch — desk research, slide drafts, basic financial benchmarks — so senior staff start at hour 5, not hour 0.
**Getting started**
1. Request access at [manus.im](http://manus.im) (now broadly available post-Meta acquisition).
2. Give it a clear goal in plain English. Watch the *Manus Computer* window to see it work.
3. Intervene mid-task to redirect.
4. Treat early outputs as a junior analyst's first draft, not the final answer.$md$, 'Butterfly Effect Pte Ltd (originally China, now Singapore). Launched March 2025. Acquired by Meta December 2025.', 'https://manus.im'),
  ('cursor', 'Cursor', 'dev-no-code', 4, 1, 'Cursor is the AI-native code editor that has effectively become the default tool for serious AI-assisted software engineering in 2026.', $md$Cursor is the AI-native code editor that has effectively become the default tool for serious AI-assisted software engineering in 2026. Technically it's a fork of Microsoft's open-source VS Code — so it inherits the entire ecosystem of extensions and feels familiar to most developers — but every part of the editor has been re-engineered around AI: Cmd-K applies natural-language inline edits, Cmd-L opens a chat with full repository context, and the Composer / Agent mode can plan and execute multi-file refactors autonomously while you watch. Crucially, Cursor indexes the whole codebase so its suggestions actually understand the cross-file context (other functions, imports, conventions, types) — which is why it has overtaken GitHub Copilot in many engineering teams. It is used by founders shipping their first product, by senior engineers refactoring legacy code, and increasingly by non-engineering "builder" roles who want to ship internal tools without filing a Jira ticket.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** A non-engineer founder uses Cursor's agent mode to ship a custom Shopify ring-sizer micro-app over a weekend — point Cursor at the repo, describe the feature in English.
- **Calo:** Internal tool builders use Cursor to extend the Crystal Ball forecasting tool's Next.js / FastAPI codebase, refactoring entire modules with confidence the agent understands cross-file context.
- **Agency:** Devs at a creative agency ship landing pages and microsites 3–5× faster, with the agent handling boilerplate while engineers focus on craft.
**Getting started**
1. Download from [cursor.com](http://cursor.com). £15/mo Pro for serious use.
2. Open a repo → Cursor indexes it for context.
3. Cmd-K for quick inline edits, Cmd-L to chat with full repo context, Composer / Agent mode for multi-file refactors.
4. Configure rules in `.cursorrules` so the agent knows your codebase conventions.$md$, 'Anysphere, 2022 (San Francisco). Founders Michael Truell, Sualeh Asif, Arvid Lunnemark, Aman Sanger.', 'https://cursor.com'),
  ('lovable', 'Lovable', 'dev-no-code', 4, 2, 'Lovable is a "vibe coding" platform built in Stockholm — you describe the web app you want in plain English, and Lovable generates a real, working full-stack application (typically React + Supabase) which you can then iterate on by continuing the conversation.', $md$Lovable is a "vibe coding" platform built in Stockholm — you describe the web app you want in plain English, and Lovable generates a real, working full-stack application (typically React + Supabase) which you can then iterate on by continuing the conversation. Where older no-code tools (Bubble, Webflow) gave you a rigid visual builder, Lovable feels more like pair-programming with an AI: you can add features ("add a leaderboard", "wire this up to Stripe", "send a Slack alert when a new user signs up"), connect a Supabase database for real data, and either publish straight to a Lovable subdomain or export the GitHub repo and host it yourself. It is one of the strongest options in 2026 for marketers, founders and ops people who need to ship a real product — quizzes, lead-gen funnels, internal tools, customer portals — without an engineering team, and the resulting code is clean enough that a developer can take it over later if needed.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Build a custom "styling quiz" lead-gen funnel that collects answers, scores intent, syncs to Klaviyo and shows tailored recommendations — without engineering involvement.
- **Calo:** Spin up an internal kitchen-snapshot dashboard for a new region: which meals shipped, complaints, repeat rates — staffed in days not months.
- **Agency:** Build bespoke client microsites and interactive campaign pages 10× faster than handing off to dev — copywriter and designer iterate live with the AI.
**Getting started**
1. Go to [lovable.dev](http://lovable.dev) → start a free project.
2. Describe the app ("I need a quiz that recommends rings based on style preferences and writes leads to Klaviyo").
3. Iterate by chatting; connect Supabase for data and Stripe for payments.
4. Publish to a Lovable subdomain or export the GitHub repo.$md$, '2023 (Stockholm, Sweden) by Anton Osika and Fabian Hedin; previously known as GPT Engineer.', 'https://lovable.dev'),
  ('replit', 'Replit', 'dev-no-code', 4, 3, 'Replit started life as an in-browser IDE — a way to write and run code from any device without setting anything up on your laptop — and has since become a complete, end-to-end "build, ship and host an app via AI agent" suite.', $md$Replit started life as an in-browser IDE — a way to write and run code from any device without setting anything up on your laptop — and has since become a complete, end-to-end "build, ship and host an app via AI agent" suite. The 2026 version is centred around Replit Agent, which can scaffold a project, write the code, set up the database, run tests, deploy, and monitor the result, all from a single natural-language prompt and all within Replit's own infrastructure. The big advantage over competitors like Lovable is that Replit handles hosting, environments, secrets and scaling natively — there's no "now connect this to Vercel and Supabase" step. It's also strong for live multiplayer collaboration (think Google Docs for code), which makes it a good fit for small teams or for showing a working prototype during a meeting. Replit has been around since 2016 and has been used by everyone from school students learning Python to founders shipping early-stage SaaS products.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Build and host a private B2B gifting portal for corporate clients — ordering, invoicing, custom engraving — without standing up DevOps.
- **Calo:** Spin up internal ops tools (delivery exception triagers, refund auto-classifiers) directly inside Replit and have engineers later harden the ones that prove their value.
- **Agency:** Use Replit Agent to prototype client app concepts in pitches — show, don't tell. Wins deals.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [replit.com](http://replit.com) (free; £20/mo Core).
2. Click *Create with Agent*, describe the app.
3. Replit deploys it on its own infrastructure — share a live URL within minutes.
4. Use *Replit Teams* for collaboration and version control.$md$, '2016 by Amjad Masad, Faris Masad and Haya Odeh (San Francisco).', 'https://replit.com'),
  ('base44', 'Base44', 'dev-no-code', 4, 4, 'Base44 is one of the purest expressions of "vibe coding" in the market — a fully chat-based AI app builder where you describe what you want and it generates a working web app, with database, authentication and deployment all bundled in.', $md$Base44 is one of the purest expressions of "vibe coding" in the market — a fully chat-based AI app builder where you describe what you want and it generates a working web app, with database, authentication and deployment all bundled in. There are no third-party integrations to configure, no Supabase setup, no Vercel deploy step; Base44 manages the whole stack behind a single conversational interface. It became a cult hit in 2025 because of its origin story — built in six months by a single solo founder, Maor Shlomo, after his Israeli reserve duty, profitable from month one, and acquired by Wix in June 2025 for \$80M plus earnouts after reaching \~250,000 users. It now operates as a distinct product within the Wix portfolio. Base44 is at its best for non-technical builders shipping internal tools (booking systems, simple CRMs, small SaaS products), and the user complaints — primarily around credit pricing and data isolation in multi-tenant apps — are worth knowing before betting a serious product on it.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** "Build a back-office app for tracking which atelier is working on which custom commission, with photo updates and customer-facing status." Base44 ships it.
- **Calo:** Build a per-region invoice and supplier-approval portal — describe the workflow once, deploy in days.
- **Agency:** Replace bespoke client dashboards (campaign performance, asset libraries) with Base44 builds — branded per client, custom logic, no engineering team.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [base44.com](http://base44.com).
2. Pick a category template or start from a prompt.
3. Iterate by chatting ("add a leaderboard", "send a Slack alert when status = urgent").
4. Publish from the same chat — Base44 handles hosting, DB and auth automatically.$md$, '2024 by Maor Shlomo (Israel). Acquired by Wix June 2025.', 'https://base44.com'),
  ('emergent', 'Emergent', 'dev-no-code', 4, 5, 'Emergent is one of the fastest-growing startups in the world — an agentic vibe-coding platform that ships *production-grade* apps from natural-language briefs by orchestrating multiple specialised AI agents (frontend, backend, database, deployment, testing) that collaborate to…', $md$Emergent is one of the fastest-growing startups in the world — an agentic vibe-coding platform that ships *production-grade* apps from natural-language briefs by orchestrating multiple specialised AI agents (frontend, backend, database, deployment, testing) that collaborate to design, build, test and deploy a full-stack application end-to-end. It launched publicly in 2025, was founded by twin brothers Mukund Jha (ex-CTO of Indian quick-commerce giant Dunzo) and Madhav Jha (PhD computer scientist, founding member of the Amazon SageMaker team), and has reportedly hit \$100M ARR within eight months from launch on the back of more than 6 million users. Emergent's distinctive pitch — versus Lovable, Base44 or Replit — is that it generates apps that are intended to be real products, not prototypes: real backends, real databases, real auth, with all generated code synced directly to your GitHub for ownership and audit. It has become a popular choice for non-technical founders, small businesses and even enterprise teams who want to skip the engineering bottleneck.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Build a private VIP wholesale portal — login per buyer, custom price lists, invoice generation — without hiring engineers.
- **Calo:** Build a region-specific operator app for kitchen managers (today's pull list, exceptions, photo verification) and ship the same week the brief is written.
- **Agency:** Productise AI tools for clients — for example, a "campaign brief generator" you license to 10 brands. Agencies are using Emergent to escape pure services and add SaaS revenue.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [emergent.sh](http://emergent.sh) (credit-based pricing).
2. Describe what you want — Emergent's agents architect, code, test and deploy.
3. All code syncs to your GitHub.
4. Iterate by chat; for serious apps, hand the repo to a developer for security review.$md$, '2024 by Mukund Jha (CEO, ex-Dunzo CTO) and Madhav Jha (CTO). San Francisco. Public launch 2025.', 'https://emergent.sh'),
  ('heygen', 'HeyGen', 'content-creation', 5, 1, 'HeyGen is the leading AI avatar and video generation platform — a tool that lets you record yourself once (a 2-minute calibration video) and then generates new videos of your avatar saying anything you type, in 175+ languages, with realistic lip-sync, in any setting.', $md$HeyGen is the leading AI avatar and video generation platform — a tool that lets you record yourself once (a 2-minute calibration video) and then generates new videos of your avatar saying anything you type, in 175+ languages, with realistic lip-sync, in any setting. The use cases break down into roughly three buckets: scaled personalised video (sales outreach, customer thank-yous), localisation (one piece of executive content distributed natively in every market), and video creation at scale for teams who don't have studio capacity (training, internal comms, social ads). HeyGen also offers stock avatars, screen recording, and an API for programmatic generation, which is what makes the personalisation use cases work — one video per customer, generated automatically. It has become one of the most-used video tools in modern marketing departments because it removes the single biggest bottleneck in video production: getting humans on camera every time you want to make something.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** The founder records once; HeyGen produces personalised "thank you for your custom order" videos addressed by name to every high-AOV customer.
- **Calo:** Localise the founder's monthly customer update video into Arabic for KSA / GCC and English for UK — same person, native lip-sync, in minutes.
- **Agency:** Create scaled video ad variants — same script, different avatars / languages — to test creative across markets without re-shoots.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [heygen.com](http://heygen.com).
2. Record a 2-minute calibration video to create your *Avatar*.
3. Type a script → choose avatar, voice and language → render.
4. Use the API for personalisation at scale (e.g. one video per customer).$md$, '2020 by Joshua Xu and Wayne Liang (Los Angeles / Shenzhen).', 'https://www.heygen.com'),
  ('synthesia', 'Synthesia', 'content-creation', 5, 2, 'Synthesia is the enterprise-grade AI video platform — a London-based company founded by academics from UCL and TU Munich, now used by more than half the Fortune 100 for internal training, customer comms and marketing video.', $md$Synthesia is the enterprise-grade AI video platform — a London-based company founded by academics from UCL and TU Munich, now used by more than half the Fortune 100 for internal training, customer comms and marketing video. It produces videos with stock or custom AI avatars in 140+ languages, with template-based workflows, screen recording, voice cloning and a level of governance (SSO, audit logs, content moderation, watermarks, indemnification) that the consumer-grade tools don't offer. Where HeyGen leans more towards creators and growth marketers, Synthesia is the choice when you need to ship video at industrial scale across a global organisation and you need legal and compliance to sign off. Typical deployments turn 30-page SOPs into 4-minute video modules, or compress weeks of L&D production into an afternoon — and let teams update those videos by editing the script rather than re-shooting.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Internal training — turn the brand's "how to talk about provenance and ethical sourcing" SOP into a polished video module for new boutique staff.
- **Calo:** Onboarding videos for new kitchen and CX hires across regions, localised once and updated monthly without re-recording.
- **Agency:** Deliver client comms videos (campaign recaps, results readouts) at the polish level of a video team, without one.
**Getting started**
1. [Synthesia.io](http://Synthesia.io) → request a demo or take Personal plan.
2. Pick an avatar and template.
3. Paste your script (or generate one with Synthesia AI).
4. Render → embed in LMS, intranet or share by link.$md$, '2017 by Victor Riparbelli, Steffen Tjerrild, Lourdes Agapito and Matthias Niessner (London).', 'https://www.synthesia.io'),
  ('descript', 'Descript', 'content-creation', 5, 3, 'Descript is the audio and video editor that flips the standard interface on its head — you edit by editing the transcript, not by trimming a waveform. Delete a sentence in the text, and that sentence is gone from the video.', $md$Descript is the audio and video editor that flips the standard interface on its head — you edit by editing the transcript, not by trimming a waveform. Delete a sentence in the text, and that sentence is gone from the video. Re-arrange paragraphs, and the underlying clip re-orders to match. On top of this core idea, Descript has layered an unusually deep set of AI tools: Studio Sound cleans up bad audio recordings to studio quality, Overdub clones your voice so you can fix mistakes by typing, AI Eye Contact corrects gaze to camera, Filler Word Removal strips "ums" automatically, and Magic Edit can generate vertical clips for socials. The combination has made Descript the default editor for podcasters, founder-led video teams and content marketers — anyone who wants to edit at the speed of writing rather than at the speed of a Premiere timeline. It was founded by Andrew Mason, the ex-Groupon founder, in 2017.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Edit founder-led Reels and TikToks at speed — cut filler words, swap mistakes via overdub, generate vertical clips for IG / TikTok / YouTube Shorts.
- **Calo:** Turn weekly all-hands recordings into clean highlight reels for non-attending team members — 60-minute meeting → 5-minute summary.
- **Agency:** Edit client podcast episodes and interviews 5× faster — copywriters can edit, not just videographers.
**Getting started**
1. Download from [descript.com](http://descript.com) (free tier; £19/mo Hobbyist+).
2. Drop in audio / video — Descript transcribes automatically.
3. Edit by deleting / rearranging text in the transcript.
4. Use *Studio Sound* to fix bad audio and *Overdub* to clone your voice for fixes.$md$, '2017 by Andrew Mason (San Francisco).', 'https://www.descript.com'),
  ('opus-clip', 'Opus Clip', 'content-creation', 5, 4, 'Opus Clip is the category-defining AI video clipping tool — feed it a long-form video (a podcast, a webinar, a livestream, a keynote) and it returns dozens of vertical, captioned, social-ready short clips, each scored by a "virality score" trained on what tends to perform on…', $md$Opus Clip is the category-defining AI video clipping tool — feed it a long-form video (a podcast, a webinar, a livestream, a keynote) and it returns dozens of vertical, captioned, social-ready short clips, each scored by a "virality score" trained on what tends to perform on TikTok, Reels and Shorts. The AI does the work of an experienced social-video editor: it finds the highlight moments, reframes for vertical, adds animated captions, picks B-roll, removes filler words, and queues everything for one-click publishing across platforms. The newer ClipAnything model handles non-talking-head video too (vlogs, sports, gaming, TV-style content) and the Agent Opus product goes further still, generating fully AI-produced short videos from a topic prompt with researcher, scriptwriter, storyboard, motion designer and voice actor agents working in concert. Opus Clip has reached more than 10M creators globally and is the engine behind the short-form output of major media brands like Audacy.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Founder runs a 30-minute brand storytelling video; Opus Clip turns it into 25 captioned vertical shorts for IG Reels, TikTok and YouTube Shorts in one go.
- **Calo:** Repurpose every long podcast appearance the founder does into 15+ short-form clips, distributed across the brand's regional accounts.
- **Agency:** Run "content multiplication" as a service — every client podcast or webinar becomes 30+ pieces of social content for the month.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [opus.pro](http://opus.pro).
2. Paste a YouTube URL or upload a video.
3. Pick clip length, branding and target platform.
4. Review the AI's clip selections, edit, then auto-publish to all socials.$md$, '2022 by Young Zhao and Grace Wang (Palo Alto / Redwood City).', 'https://www.opus.pro'),
  ('beehiiv', 'Beehiiv', 'content-creation', 5, 5, 'Beehiiv is a newsletter platform built by ex-Morning Brew operators — people who actually scaled a newsletter business to millions of readers and hundreds of millions of dollars, and who built Beehiiv as the tool they wished they''d had.', $md$Beehiiv is a newsletter platform built by ex-Morning Brew operators — people who actually scaled a newsletter business to millions of readers and hundreds of millions of dollars, and who built Beehiiv as the tool they wished they'd had. Compared to Mailchimp or older platforms, Beehiiv is faster, looks dramatically better out of the box, and bakes in monetisation natively: native ad placements (with a marketplace of advertisers), referral programs, paid subscriptions, recommendations between newsletters, and partner Boosts that pay you per qualified subscriber acquired. The AI layer covers subject-line optimisation, magic post drafting, audience summaries, and personalised content recommendations. It has become the default platform for serious modern newsletter builders — both individuals and brands — because it treats a newsletter like the media business it actually is, rather than like a glorified email list.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Run a high-design weekly editorial newsletter ("This week in fine jewellery") — Beehiiv's design templates make it look like a magazine; native ads can offset the cost.
- **Calo:** Launch a regional nutrition / health editorial newsletter ("The Calo Weekly") in each market — proper editorial content, not just promo emails.
- **Agency:** Run an industry insights newsletter as a lead-magnet for the agency itself; Beehiiv's referral program drives organic list growth.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [beehiiv.com](http://beehiiv.com) (generous free tier).
2. Pick a design template, set up sender domain and DNS.
3. Use AI Subject Line Optimiser and Magic Posts (AI drafting).
4. Turn on *Boosts* / *Referrals* once you have a few thousand subscribers.$md$, '2021 by Tyler Denk, Benjamin Hargett and Jake Hurd (New York).', 'https://www.beehiiv.com'),
  ('gamma', 'Gamma', 'content-creation', 5, 6, 'Gamma is an AI-native presentation, document and webpage generator that has quickly become the modern alternative to PowerPoint, Keynote and [Beautiful.ai](http://Beautiful.ai).', $md$Gamma is an AI-native presentation, document and webpage generator that has quickly become the modern alternative to PowerPoint, Keynote and [Beautiful.ai](http://Beautiful.ai). You describe what you want — "build me a 10-slide deck pitching our Q2 marketing strategy" or "create a one-pager landing page for our new collection" — paste an outline, or upload a doc, and Gamma produces a polished, branded result that's noticeably above the generic AI aesthetic. Underneath, it generates a proper layout system (think: a slide-by-slide design system, not a static template), so subsequent edits via chat ("make this section more visual", "swap the chart for a quote") work cleanly. You can export to PowerPoint or PDF, share a live web link, or embed it as a webpage. For marketing and strategy teams, the practical effect is that senior people spend dramatically less time wrestling with slide-masters and more time on the actual narrative.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Generate a wholesale linesheet / lookbook PDF directly from product data — saves a designer week of layout.
- **Calo:** Build the weekly leadership update deck from a Notion bullet list — Gamma turns it into a polished, on-brand deck in 60 seconds.
- **Agency:** Pitch decks at speed — paste the proposal narrative, set the brand theme, export. Senior strategists stop being slide monkeys.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [gamma.app](http://gamma.app) (generous free tier; £8–£15/mo Pro/Plus).
2. Click *Create new* → describe the deck or paste an outline.
3. Pick a brand theme; refine slides via chat ("make this section more visual").
4. Export to PPT or PDF, or share as a live web link.$md$, '2020 by Grant Lee, Jon Noronha and James Fox (San Francisco).', 'https://gamma.app'),
  ('chatbase', 'Chatbase', 'content-creation', 5, 7, 'Chatbase is the leading platform for building branded, AI-powered chat agents trained on your own content — your product docs, support knowledge base, website URLs, Notion workspace, past tickets, FAQs.', $md$Chatbase is the leading platform for building branded, AI-powered chat agents trained on your own content — your product docs, support knowledge base, website URLs, Notion workspace, past tickets, FAQs. The 2026 version has gone far beyond simple FAQ bots: Chatbase agents can take real actions through API integrations and connections to CRMs, payment systems, scheduling tools and ticketing systems, meaning a customer-facing agent can not only answer "where's my order?" but actually issue the refund, reschedule the delivery or update the booking — all from inside a chat conversation. It's used by 10,000+ businesses and has been bootstrapped to \~\$8M ARR by founder Yasser Elsaid, which is unusual in the AI space and tends to mean the product is engineered for revenue, not for show. The agents can be embedded on a website, Slack, WhatsApp or Intercom, with SOC 2 Type II and GDPR compliance.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** A site chat agent trained on care guides, sizing, returns and bespoke commissioning — handles 80% of pre-sale and post-purchase enquiries that currently hit human CX.
- **Calo:** A region-specific support agent (UK / KSA / UAE) trained on the menu, allergens, delivery windows and pause / cancel flows — connected to Zendesk so it can actually take action.
- **Agency:** White-label the agent for clients — every client gets a branded "AI on their site" service the agency manages.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [chatbase.co](http://chatbase.co).
2. Train an agent on URLs, PDFs, Notion or Q&A pairs.
3. Customise tone, branding, fallback to human, and add API actions.
4. Embed via script tag, or deploy on WhatsApp, Slack, Intercom.$md$, '2022 by Yasser Elsaid (bootstrapped to \$8M+ ARR).', 'https://www.chatbase.co'),
  ('midjourney', 'Midjourney', 'visuals-audio', 6, 1, 'Midjourney is the gold standard for AI image generation when *aesthetic* is what matters most — the model is famously tuned for editorial, fashion and luxury sensibilities, and remains the favourite of art directors and creative strategists despite increasingly capable…', $md$Midjourney is the gold standard for AI image generation when *aesthetic* is what matters most — the model is famously tuned for editorial, fashion and luxury sensibilities, and remains the favourite of art directors and creative strategists despite increasingly capable competitors (DALL-E 3, GPT-Image, Imagen, Flux, Ideogram). What sets it apart is taste rather than raw fidelity: prompts that produce mood, atmosphere, lighting and composition with an unusually strong "this looks like a real magazine cover" quality. The 2026 version has the long-overdue web app, video generation, character and style references for consistency across a campaign, in-app editing and upscaling, and Vary Region for tweaking parts of an image. Marketing teams typically use Midjourney earlier in the pipeline — for moodboards, concept art, briefing photographers — rather than as the final asset, because that's where it adds the most lift over a stock photo or human-photographed shot.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Generate editorial concept imagery for a campaign — moody close-ups of rings on textured backgrounds — to brief the photographer or use directly in social.
- **Calo:** Concept hero food imagery for new menu items before the food photography shoot — agree the visual direction internally with the chef before booking studio.
- **Agency:** Mood-boards and concept frames at the speed of thought — present 6 visual directions in a pitch instead of 1.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [midjourney.com](http://midjourney.com) (£8–£48/mo).
2. Use the web app's image prompts: text + reference images + style refs.
3. Lock a *Style Reference* code per brand for consistency across generations.
4. Upscale, vary, edit in-app.$md$, '2021 by David Holz (San Francisco). Originally Discord-only; web app launched 2024.', 'https://www.midjourney.com'),
  ('runway', 'Runway', 'visuals-audio', 6, 2, 'Runway is one of the original AI video companies and remains one of the strongest creative suites in 2026 — spanning text-to-video, image-to-video, video-to-video, motion brush, frame interpolation, green-screen removal, AI rotoscoping and a constantly-evolving set of in-app…', $md$Runway is one of the original AI video companies and remains one of the strongest creative suites in 2026 — spanning text-to-video, image-to-video, video-to-video, motion brush, frame interpolation, green-screen removal, AI rotoscoping and a constantly-evolving set of in-app tools that wouldn't look out of place in a Hollywood VFX house. The flagship Gen-4 model produces minute-long generations with strong character and scene consistency, and Act One lets you drive an animated avatar's performance with a phone video of yourself acting it out. Runway has serious credibility in the film industry — its tools have been used in real productions including Oscar-nominated films — and that translates into a more director-led toolset: cinematographic prompts, fine motion control, layered editing. For marketers, Runway is at its best when you need short cinematic moments to extend or augment a real shoot, rather than fully replace one.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Animate static product photography — a still of a necklace becomes a 5-second cinematic shot of it being lifted from a velvet box.
- **Calo:** Pre-visualise a TV / OOH campaign before commissioning a film crew — agree the look-and-feel cheaply, shoot the real thing with confidence.
- **Agency:** Generate ad concept films for client pitches; supplement live-action shoots with AI b-roll.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [runwayml.com](http://runwayml.com) (£12–£76/mo Pro/Unlimited).
2. Use *Gen-4* for text- and image-to-video.
3. Use *Act One* to drive an avatar's performance from your own phone video.
4. Stitch generations together in the in-app editor.$md$, '2018 by Cristóbal Valenzuela, Anastasis Germanidis and Alejandro Matamala (New York).', 'https://runwayml.com'),
  ('kling', 'Kling', 'visuals-audio', 6, 3, 'Kling is a Chinese-origin AI video model from Kuaishou (TikTok''s main domestic rival in China) that competes credibly at the frontier with OpenAI''s Sora and Google''s Veo, particularly for cinematic, physically-realistic motion and complex camera work.', $md$Kling is a Chinese-origin AI video model from Kuaishou (TikTok's main domestic rival in China) that competes credibly at the frontier with OpenAI's Sora and Google's Veo, particularly for cinematic, physically-realistic motion and complex camera work. It is unusually strong for human movement — gait, fight choreography, hands and faces in motion — which is one of the harder problems in AI video, and which makes it a popular choice for narrative, fashion and lifestyle content rather than abstract or stylised shots. Kling is available directly via [klingai.com](http://klingai.com) and increasingly through aggregators like Higgsfield, where you can switch between Kling, Veo, Sora and other models on the same prompt to compare outputs. For most marketers, Kling is the right pick when you need believable real-world motion at a noticeably lower cost-per-generation than Sora 2 or Veo 3.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Create cinematic 10-second product hero films for hero SKUs — a ring rotating slowly under cinematic lighting — for paid social.
- **Calo:** Generate "hero meal" cinematic shots for a campaign without booking a food cinematographer (£5k+ a day).
- **Agency:** Compete with Sora / Veo / Runway on cost — Kling often produces better results for human-centred shots at lower price points.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [klingai.com](http://klingai.com).
2. Buy credits (per-generation pricing).
3. Use text-to-video or image-to-video; control camera motion via parameters.
4. Most marketers use Kling via aggregators like Higgsfield (see below) for one combined workflow.$md$, 'Kuaishou Technology, model launched June 2024.', 'https://klingai.com'),
  ('flora', 'Flora', 'visuals-audio', 6, 4, 'Flora is a creative environment built around an infinite canvas where every major AI image and video model — Nano Banana / Nano Banana Pro, Veo 3.1, Seedance 2.0, Sora 2, GPT Image, Wan 2.6, Runway Gen-4, Aleph, Kling and many others — sits in a single workspace, alongside…', $md$Flora is a creative environment built around an infinite canvas where every major AI image and video model — Nano Banana / Nano Banana Pro, Veo 3.1, Seedance 2.0, Sora 2, GPT Image, Wan 2.6, Runway Gen-4, Aleph, Kling and many others — sits in a single workspace, alongside FAUNA, the in-product creative agent that suggests directions, generates variations and helps you iterate without leaving the canvas. The pitch isn't yet-another-model; it's a unified place to think visually: ideate by exploring hundreds of possibilities across modalities, iterate in real time with the rest of the creative team, and then scale a single concept into hundreds of production-grade, on-brand assets. Flora has been adopted by serious creative shops including Pentagram, Lionsgate and major fashion houses, and is positioned as the "creative environment" rather than just another generator — closer in spirit to Figma's relationship to design than to a single-purpose AI app. The most important difference vs. Higgsfield is the canvas-first, multiplayer, Figma-style workflow rather than a templated marketer-oriented studio.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Run an entire campaign on one Flora canvas — start with Nano Banana / Midjourney for editorial stills, animate the chosen direction with Veo 3.1, generate on-figure variants with Seedance 2.0, and export production-ready assets — with the team commenting and iterating live in the same workspace.
- **Calo:** Build a hero food-photography canvas where the menu team and brand team can explore, vote and lock visual direction across regions before any real shoot is booked — and use FAUNA to surface "directions you didn't ask for" that the team might otherwise miss.
- **Agency:** Replace the messy [moodboard-plus-Frame.io](http://moodboard-plus-Frame.io)-plus-Figma stack with one creative environment per pitch; review, generate, comment and ship from a single canvas.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [flora.ai](http://flora.ai) (free tier; paid plans for production volume).
2. Open a new project on the infinite canvas; pick from 50+ models in the model picker.
3. Use FAUNA to suggest follow-up generations and explore variations automatically.
4. Invite collaborators — Flora is multiplayer by default and built for real-time creative review.$md$, 'Florafauna AI. Public launch 2024.', 'https://flora.ai'),
  ('higgsfield', 'Higgsfield', 'visuals-audio', 6, 5, 'Higgsfield is a full AI video creative workspace built specifically for marketers and social-first creators — rather than picking one model and staking the company on it, Higgsfield aggregates the best video models on the market (Kling, Veo 3.1, Sora 2, Seedance 2.0, plus its…', $md$Higgsfield is a full AI video creative workspace built specifically for marketers and social-first creators — rather than picking one model and staking the company on it, Higgsfield aggregates the best video models on the market (Kling, Veo 3.1, Sora 2, Seedance 2.0, plus its own proprietary Soul / DOP / Cinema Studio models) into a single workspace, and adds the workflows marketers actually need on top. Click-to-Ad takes a product URL and generates 3–5 short-form social ads ready to test in Meta. Sora 2 Trends matches your brand to whichever short-form video format is currently going viral. Cinema Studio gives serious filmmakers per-shot camera, lens and motion control. The company was founded in late 2023 by Alex Mashrabov (the former head of Generative AI at Snap, and the original creator of Snap Lenses) and has scaled to a \$200M annualised revenue run rate by early 2026, making it one of the fastest-growing video startups ever.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Drop a product URL into *Click-to-Ad* — Higgsfield generates 3–5 short-form social video ad variants in different styles, ready to test in Meta.
- **Calo:** Build a library of seasonal lifestyle hero videos (Ramadan, summer, fitness, detox) by combining product photos with cinematic AI-generated environments.
- **Agency:** Replace the "production" line item in social retainers — produce dozens of paid social video variants per week per client at a fraction of the cost.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [higgsfield.ai](http://higgsfield.ai) (£10–£34+/mo, model-dependent credit cost).
2. Try *Click-to-Ad* with a product URL for the fastest first win.
3. Use *Cinema Studio* for shot-by-shot control with cinematic camera presets.
4. Switch models per shot (Kling for human motion, Veo for realism, Seedance for stylised).$md$, 'October 2023 by Alex Mashrabov (ex-Snap, head of Generative AI), Yerzat Dulat and Mahi de Silva (San Francisco).', 'https://higgsfield.ai'),
  ('veo', 'Veo', 'visuals-audio', 6, 6, 'Veo is Google DeepMind''s flagship video generation model and is generally considered the highest-realism video model on the market in 2026 for a wide range of marketing use cases — particularly anything involving real-world physics, natural lighting, complex environments, and…', $md$Veo is Google DeepMind's flagship video generation model and is generally considered the highest-realism video model on the market in 2026 for a wide range of marketing use cases — particularly anything involving real-world physics, natural lighting, complex environments, and shots where the slightest "AI tell" would break the illusion. The headline feature in Veo 3 / 3.1 is that it generates synchronised audio (voice, ambience, music) alongside the video, rather than producing silent footage that has to be scored separately, which is a meaningful workflow saving. It is available to consumers via Gemini Advanced / Google AI Pro, in Flow (Google's own AI filmmaking workspace), and for production use at scale via Vertex AI. Most marketers will encounter Veo through aggregators like Higgsfield rather than directly, and will reserve it for the highest-stakes hero shots where realism matters most.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Generate ultra-realistic "hero hand-shot" videos — a hand reaching for a ring on a marble countertop — usable in paid social.
- **Calo:** Generate hyper-realistic kitchen / chef b-roll for the brand film, supplementing rather than replacing real shoots.
- **Agency:** Use Veo for the highest-stakes hero shots in a campaign film where physical realism is non-negotiable.
**Getting started**
1. Access Veo via Gemini Advanced / Google AI Pro or via Vertex AI for production use.
2. For marketers, easiest route is via Higgsfield or Flow (Google's own AI filmmaking workspace).
3. Use detailed cinematographic prompts (lens, lighting, motion).
4. Generate iteratively — pick the best frame as a starting point for the next pass.$md$, 'Google DeepMind. Veo 1 launched May 2024; Veo 3 / 3.1 in late 2025.', 'https://deepmind.google/technologies/veo'),
  ('elevenlabs', 'ElevenLabs', 'visuals-audio', 6, 7, 'ElevenLabs is the runaway leader in AI voice — natural-sounding text-to-speech, voice cloning from as little as a minute of source audio, and dubbing across 30+ languages while retaining the original speaker''s vocal identity (so a founder''s English brand video can be dubbed into…', $md$ElevenLabs is the runaway leader in AI voice — natural-sounding text-to-speech, voice cloning from as little as a minute of source audio, and dubbing across 30+ languages while retaining the original speaker's vocal identity (so a founder's English brand video can be dubbed into Arabic in their own voice rather than a stranger's). The product has been adopted by everyone from indie podcasters and audiobook narrators to Fortune 500 brands and Hollywood studios; it is also one of the few AI products that tend to make non-believers immediately understand what's possible — most people can't reliably tell its output from a real recording. The wider product set now includes Studio for long-form audio production (audiobooks, podcasts), Dubbing for full-video translation, the Conversational AI platform for voice agents, and a marketplace of stock voices with proper licensing and consent records.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Dub the founder's English brand video into Arabic, French and Mandarin — same voice, native pronunciation — for international micro-launches.
- **Calo:** Voice the IVR / voice agent in the founder's voice across UK and GCC, in English and Arabic, with consistent tone.
- **Agency:** Voice every social ad variant without hiring VO talent for each test — clone the brand voice once, generate dozens of variants.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [elevenlabs.io](http://elevenlabs.io) (free; £4–£18/mo for serious use).
2. Clone a voice from a 1-minute sample (with consent) or use a stock voice.
3. Type a script, generate, download.
4. Use Studio for long-form (audiobooks, podcasts) and Dubbing for video translation.$md$, '2022 by Piotr Dabkowski and Mati Staniszewski (London / New York).', 'https://elevenlabs.io'),
  ('suno', 'Suno', 'visuals-audio', 6, 8, 'Suno is a generative music platform that produces full songs — vocals, instrumentation, structure, lyrics — from a single text prompt, with surprisingly good quality across genres from acoustic singer-songwriter to hip-hop to cinematic orchestral.', $md$Suno is a generative music platform that produces full songs — vocals, instrumentation, structure, lyrics — from a single text prompt, with surprisingly good quality across genres from acoustic singer-songwriter to hip-hop to cinematic orchestral. The marketing use case is direct: instead of hunting through Epidemic Sound or paying sync licences, brands can generate fully owned, royalty-free music tailored to a specific campaign, region or even individual social clip, with their own brand-defining sonic identity. The free tier is generous enough to demo, the paid tiers grant clear commercial use rights, and the model is now competent enough that several brand campaigns have shipped with Suno-generated soundtracks without it being detectable. The best marketing teams treat it as a strategic asset (own your sonic brand) rather than a stock-music substitute. Suno was founded by ex-Kensho researchers in Cambridge, Massachusetts.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Generate a custom soundtrack for the brand film and seasonal Reels — owned, royalty-free, on-brand, in a style no competitor has.
- **Calo:** Region-specific brand jingles — an upbeat track for UK Reels, a different tonal palette for KSA — without buying a sync licence.
- **Agency:** Score every social cut differently — pitch decks no longer all use the same Epidemic Sound stock track.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [suno.com](http://suno.com) (free tier; £8–£24/mo).
2. Describe the song ("warm acoustic, mid-tempo, female vocal, subtle strings").
3. Generate, regenerate, extend.
4. Check the licence terms — paid plans grant commercial use rights.$md$, '2022 by Mikey Shulman, Georg Kucsko, Martin Camacho and Keenan Freyberg (Cambridge, Mass.).', 'https://suno.com'),
  ('artlist', 'Artlist', 'visuals-audio', 6, 9, 'Artlist is the creator-economy stock platform of choice — royalty-free music, sound effects, stock footage, motion graphics templates and (increasingly) AI tools, all available under one annual subscription with full commercial use rights and proper indemnification.', $md$Artlist is the creator-economy stock platform of choice — royalty-free music, sound effects, stock footage, motion graphics templates and (increasingly) AI tools, all available under one annual subscription with full commercial use rights and proper indemnification. Where Suno gives you generative music and Midjourney gives you generated images, Artlist gives you the licensing-safe alternative for the moments when human-made, fully cleared content is the right call — the brand film going on TV, the campaign that needs an actual band's track, the hero asset where the legal team won't sign off on AI. The library is curated to a strong editorial standard, the licensing model is unusually clean (one subscription covers all your channels including paid ads), and the pricing is friendly enough that it tends to be subscribed at agency or brand level rather than per-project. Founded in Israel in 2016, Artlist has become the default for serious creators who care about both craft and cleared rights.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Source moody, editorial-feeling B-roll and music for hero brand films when stock works better than AI generation.
- **Calo:** License music for every social video globally on one annual subscription — no per-video sync clearances.
- **Agency:** Subscribe once at the agency level, deliver fully cleared assets across all client projects.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [artlist.io](http://artlist.io) (£12–£26/mo annual).
2. Subscribe at *Pro* level for full commercial coverage including paid ads.
3. Search by mood / tempo / theme.
4. Download → drop into the edit; license is auto-attached.$md$, '2016 by Eyal Raz, Itzik Elbaz, Assaf Ayalon and Ira Belsky (Israel).', 'https://artlist.io'),
  ('canva', 'Canva', 'automation', 7, 1, 'Canva is the default visual creation tool for marketing teams worldwide — a browser-based design platform that took the parts of Photoshop and InDesign that non-designers actually need and made them genuinely accessible, originally via templates and now increasingly via AI.', $md$Canva is the default visual creation tool for marketing teams worldwide — a browser-based design platform that took the parts of Photoshop and InDesign that non-designers actually need and made them genuinely accessible, originally via templates and now increasingly via AI. The 2026 version sits behind a Magic Studio AI suite that includes Magic Write (copy generation), Magic Switch (resize one design across every social and ad format in one click), Magic Edit (prompt-based image editing), text-to-image generation, AI translation and an AI video editor. Combined with Brand Kits — fonts, colours, logos, locked templates — Canva is what allows non-designer marketers across regional teams to ship on-brand work at speed, without flooding the design team with tickets. The flip side is that "Canva look" has become its own aesthetic; serious brand teams still tend to keep hero work in Figma or with external designers and use Canva for volume and velocity.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Lock the brand kit (fonts, colours, logo) and have non-designers produce on-brand IG, web banners and email graphics — with Magic Switch resizing one design across every format.
- **Calo:** Regional marketing managers in each country produce localised versions of central campaign assets in minutes — central brand stays consistent.
- **Agency:** Empower account managers and strategists to mock up concepts in pitches, freeing up designers for high-craft work.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [canva.com](http://canva.com).
2. Set up *Brand Kits* (fonts, colours, logos, templates).
3. Use *Magic Studio* for AI generation, edit-by-prompt and translation.
4. Use *Canva Teams* for shared brand control and approvals.$md$, '2013 by Melanie Perkins, Cliff Obrecht and Cameron Adams (Sydney).', 'https://www.canva.com'),
  ('figma', 'Figma', 'automation', 7, 2, 'Figma is the browser-native design tool that effectively won the design industry over the last decade — multiplayer collaboration in the browser, no installs, no exporting files back and forth, real-time cursors, design systems built natively into the tool — and was acquired by…', $md$Figma is the browser-native design tool that effectively won the design industry over the last decade — multiplayer collaboration in the browser, no installs, no exporting files back and forth, real-time cursors, design systems built natively into the tool — and was acquired by Adobe before that deal famously collapsed under regulatory pressure. The 2026 product is now significantly more than a design tool: AI features (Figma Make, First Draft, FigJam AI) bake AI into wireframing, copy generation, design system creation and component scaffolding; Figma Sites lets designers ship live, editable websites without a developer hand-off; FigJam covers the whiteboarding and workshop layer; and Dev Mode formalises the bridge to engineering. For brand and marketing teams, Figma is the place where serious design happens and where the brand's design system actually lives — not just the artefacts but the rules.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Design every site landing page, email and ad in Figma; use *Figma Make* to ship landing pages directly without dev hand-off.
- **Calo:** Build a regional design system for each market that keeps creative on-brand globally; let regional marketers use that system to self-serve.
- **Agency:** All creative happens in Figma. Use *FigJam AI* to facilitate workshops, *First Draft* to generate UI explorations, and *Figma Sites* to hand clients live, editable webpages.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [figma.com](http://figma.com) (free tier).
2. Set up a design system / component library per brand.
3. Turn on AI features in account settings.
4. Use *Dev Mode* to hand off cleanly; use *Figma Make* / *Sites* if there's no dev capacity at all.$md$, '2012 by Dylan Field and Evan Wallace (San Francisco). Public launch 2016.', 'https://www.figma.com'),
  ('designs-ai', 'Designs.ai', 'automation', 7, 3, '[Designs.ai](http://Designs.ai) is an all-in-one AI creative suite aimed squarely at non-designers and small marketing teams that need volume creative output without hiring a designer.', $md$[Designs.ai](http://Designs.ai) is an all-in-one AI creative suite aimed squarely at non-designers and small marketing teams that need volume creative output without hiring a designer. Under one subscription it bundles Logomaker (AI logo generation with brand kit extraction), Videomaker (turn a script into a finished video), Designmaker (banners, social posts, brand identity assets), Speechmaker (AI voiceovers and jingles), and Imagemaker (text-to-image with on-brand styling). The pitch is essentially "Canva, but with the AI generation deeper in the workflow" — and where it shines is when you need ten different assets for the same campaign across formats, languages and channels in a single afternoon. It's notably not the choice for hero brand work where craft matters most, but for the long tail of "we need this asset, on-brand, by 5pm" it removes a lot of friction. *Note: the icon labelled simply "Design" in the original pyramid is ambiguous; this is the most likely match given the category and visual style.*
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Generate ten logo concepts for a sub-line launch in an hour for internal review before committing to a designer.
- **Calo:** Produce social banner sets for every regional promotion at speed — same creative, multiple aspect ratios.
- **Agency:** Use as a junior-designer accelerator for low-stakes, high-volume work; senior creatives focus on the hero campaign.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [designs.ai](http://designs.ai).
2. Pick the right module: Logomaker, Videomaker, Designmaker, Speechmaker.
3. Generate variants, refine the one you like.
4. Export with brand kit applied.$md$, '2018 (Malaysia / Inmagine Group).', 'https://designs.ai'),
  ('lindy', 'Lindy', 'automation', 7, 4, 'Lindy is a no-code AI agent platform — often described as the "Zapier of AI agents" — that lets you build agents which read your inbox, run your meetings, manage your CRM, qualify leads, automate customer support and more, all by describing what you want them to do in plain…', $md$Lindy is a no-code AI agent platform — often described as the "Zapier of AI agents" — that lets you build agents which read your inbox, run your meetings, manage your CRM, qualify leads, automate customer support and more, all by describing what you want them to do in plain English. With 1,600+ native integrations (Gmail, Slack, Calendar, HubSpot, Salesforce, Notion, Linear and many more) plus a Virtual Cloud Computer mode that can drive a real browser when no API exists, Lindy can plausibly replace several rounds of headcount in the right setup — meeting recorders, email triagers, SDR workflows, customer support overflow. It was founded by Flo Crivello (ex-Uber PM, founder of Teamflow) after a hard pivot from his previous virtual office product, and has since become one of the fastest-growing AI agent companies, used heavily by founders, small business owners and increasingly by ops teams inside larger companies.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** A Lindy agent that triages every inbound email — VIP customer / wholesale enquiry / press / spam — and routes accordingly with a draft reply.
- **Calo:** Build a "meeting note" Lindy that joins every leadership Zoom, transcribes, summarises into Notion and pushes action items to the right owners in Slack.
- **Agency:** A new-business Lindy that monitors LinkedIn signals (job changes, raises, launches) for target accounts and drafts personalised outbound — no SDR needed.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [lindy.ai](http://lindy.ai).
2. Pick a template (Email Triage, Meeting Recorder, Sales Outreach).
3. Connect Gmail / Slack / Calendar / HubSpot etc.
4. Iterate by giving the agent feedback in plain English.$md$, '2023 by Flo Crivello (San Francisco; previously founder of Teamflow, ex-Uber PM).', 'https://www.lindy.ai'),
  ('n8n', 'n8n', 'automation', 7, 5, 'n8n (pronounced "n-eight-n", short for "nodemation") is the most credible open-source alternative to Zapier and Make — a fair-source, self-hostable workflow automation platform with a visual node-based builder, deep AI Agent nodes, and the option to drop into JavaScript for…', $md$n8n (pronounced "n-eight-n", short for "nodemation") is the most credible open-source alternative to Zapier and Make — a fair-source, self-hostable workflow automation platform with a visual node-based builder, deep AI Agent nodes, and the option to drop into JavaScript for anything the no-code layer can't express. Because you can self-host on your own infrastructure (or use n8n Cloud if you'd rather not), it has become the default choice for technical marketers, growth engineers and ops teams who want full control over data, costs, and the ability to chain LLM calls and HTTP requests without paying per-task fees. The AI Agent node in particular has made n8n competitive for building autonomous workflows that go well beyond "if-this-then-that": classify an inbound, decide what to do, call the right APIs, and write back the result — all on infrastructure you own. Founded in Berlin in 2019 by Jan Oberhauser.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** A flow that watches new Shopify orders, enriches each customer (Clearbit), classifies LTV potential with an LLM, and routes high-value buyers into a personalised outreach sequence.
- **Calo:** Build an internal pipeline that pulls daily Zoho Books data, runs the Crystal Ball forecast, dumps results into Notion, and pings #leadership in Slack with a colour-coded summary.
- **Agency:** Create reusable AI workflows (lead enrichment, content multiplication, reporting) and license them per client — own the IP, collect recurring revenue.
**Getting started**
1. Self-host (Docker) or use n8n Cloud (£18+/mo).
2. Drag-and-drop nodes; chain LLM calls, HTTP requests, app integrations.
3. Use *AI Agent* nodes for autonomous flows.
4. Templates marketplace covers most common patterns.$md$, '2019 by Jan Oberhauser (Berlin).', 'https://n8n.io'),
  ('make', 'Make', 'automation', 7, 6, 'Make (formerly Integromat) is a visual automation platform that sits in the same category as Zapier but goes meaningfully deeper — it''s built around a canvas where you draw the workflow, including branches, error handlers, loops, aggregators and routers, which makes it the right…', $md$Make (formerly Integromat) is a visual automation platform that sits in the same category as Zapier but goes meaningfully deeper — it's built around a canvas where you draw the workflow, including branches, error handlers, loops, aggregators and routers, which makes it the right tool when an automation has more than a few "if" statements in it. The 2026 product has a strong AI layer: AI scenario suggestions, native modules for OpenAI / Claude / Gemini / Perplexity, and a growing set of "AI agent" templates. It's used heavily inside ops-heavy marketing teams (large e-commerce and DTC operations especially) where the workflows become genuinely complex — multi-step post-purchase journeys, multi-region pricing logic, custom finance reporting — and where Zapier starts to feel constrained. Make was founded in Brno, Czech Republic in 2012 as Integromat and rebranded after being acquired by Celonis in 2020.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** A scenario that handles the full post-purchase journey — Shopify → enrichment → Klaviyo → SMS → review request → loyalty tier update — all visually mapped.
- **Calo:** Sync per-region marketing spend from Meta / Google Ads into Sheets, then into the Notion weekly report — replaces a person's Monday morning.
- **Agency:** Build complex client onboarding scenarios — new client signed → contract sent → folders created in Drive → Slack channel set up → tasks created in Asana — all automated.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [make.com](http://make.com) (generous free tier).
2. Build *Scenarios* visually; use the AI assistant to draft scenario logic.
3. Use the OpenAI / Claude / Gemini modules as nodes within scenarios.
4. Monitor execution history to debug.$md$, '2012 as Integromat by Ondřej Karas, Patrik Šimek and Roman Bíro (Czech Republic). Rebranded to Make in 2022.', 'https://www.make.com'),
  ('zapier', 'Zapier', 'automation', 7, 7, 'Zapier is the original no-code automation platform — the tool that taught a generation of operators what "API integration" even meant — and is still the default first stop for connecting 7,000+ apps with simple triggers and actions ("when X happens in app A, do Y in app B").', $md$Zapier is the original no-code automation platform — the tool that taught a generation of operators what "API integration" even meant — and is still the default first stop for connecting 7,000+ apps with simple triggers and actions ("when X happens in app A, do Y in app B"). The 2026 version is much more than that, though: Zapier Agents bring autonomous AI agents into the workflow, Zapier Tables provides a lightweight built-in database, Zapier Interfaces turns any workflow into a small front-end app, and AI by Zapier embeds LLM calls (with major-model routing) inside any step. The combined effect is that Zapier has quietly become a credible "lightweight SaaS in a box" for ops teams who want to ship internal tools without a developer. Where it tends to lose ground to n8n or Make is on complex branching logic and self-hosting, but for breadth of integrations and time-to-first-working-automation it's still the leader.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Every new Typeform "bespoke commission" submission triggers Zaps — Slack alert to the studio, draft email reply, Notion entry created, calendar slot held.
- **Calo:** Connect Zoho Books → Sheets → Notion → Slack so finance updates flow automatically; use Zapier Agents for spend approvals.
- **Agency:** Standardise the agency's internal stack — every new project, new hire, or new client triggers a chain of automations across Slack, Notion, Drive and HubSpot.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [zapier.com](http://zapier.com) (free; £15+/mo for serious use).
2. Start from a *Zap template* (there are thousands).
3. Add AI steps via *AI by Zapier* or direct ChatGPT / Claude actions.
4. Use *Zapier Tables* + *Interfaces* to build small internal apps without code.$md$, '2011 by Wade Foster, Bryan Helmig and Mike Knoop (originally Missouri).', 'https://zapier.com'),
  ('apollo', 'Apollo', 'automation', 7, 8, '[Apollo.io](http://Apollo.io) is an all-in-one B2B sales engagement and prospecting platform — a single tool that combines a 270M+ contact and 60M+ company database, intent data, sequence automation, dialer, meeting scheduler, deal management, and an increasingly capable AI…', $md$[Apollo.io](http://Apollo.io) is an all-in-one B2B sales engagement and prospecting platform — a single tool that combines a 270M+ contact and 60M+ company database, intent data, sequence automation, dialer, meeting scheduler, deal management, and an increasingly capable AI layer (AI personalised emails, AI research summaries on every prospect, AI coaching and even an AI dialler for outbound calls). Where you'd previously have stitched together ZoomInfo + Outreach + Gong + a separate dialler + a CRM, Apollo collapses much of that into one product, which is why it has been adopted aggressively by B2B-leaning startups and SMBs. For consumer-leaning businesses it has a particular use case: standing up B2B sales motions next to the core consumer business — corporate gifting for jewellery brands, corporate catering and wellness for food brands, partnerships for any DTC. Founded in 2015 in San Francisco.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Build the corporate gifting channel — Apollo to find HR / People Ops leads at UK companies of 50+, AI-personalised outbound, sequenced over 4 weeks.
- **Calo:** Drive B2B catering / corporate-wellness sales — find office managers, HRDs and wellbeing leads in target accounts across UK and GCC, and run AI-personalised cadences.
- **Agency:** Power the agency's own new-business engine — target CMOs at brands matching the ideal client profile, with AI-personalised first-touch emails.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [apollo.io](http://apollo.io) (free tier with limited credits).
2. Build a saved search that matches the ICP.
3. Use *Sequences* with AI-personalised first lines.
4. Use *Apollo AI* for research summaries on each prospect before sending.$md$, '2015 by Tim Zheng, Ray Li and Roy Chung (San Francisco).', 'https://www.apollo.io'),
  ('clay', 'Clay', 'automation', 7, 9, 'Clay is the AI-native data enrichment and go-to-market platform that has become the secret weapon of every modern outbound team.', $md$Clay is the AI-native data enrichment and go-to-market platform that has become the secret weapon of every modern outbound team. The core idea is a spreadsheet-like Table, but each column can be an enrichment from one of 75+ data providers (Apollo, ZoomInfo, LinkedIn, Twitter, Crunchbase, Builtwith, Hunter, etc.) or an AI column that uses Claygent — Clay's in-house AI agent — to research a particular fact about each row by browsing the web. The result is that you can take a list of 5,000 companies and, in a single workflow, pull their funding stage, headcount, tech stack, recent press, key personas and a custom-written first-line for each — then push the enriched list into Apollo, HubSpot, Salesforce or Smartlead for outreach. Clay has become so central to modern GTM that "Clay-as-a-service" is now a viable agency offering in its own right. Founded in New York in 2017.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Build a wholesale prospecting list — pull every UK fine-jewellery boutique from Apollo / Google Maps, enrich with Instagram followers, recent press, owner emails, and rank by fit.
- **Calo:** Build per-region B2B catering target lists with deep enrichment — office headcount, recent funding, in-office days policy, food vendor signals — and route to AI-personalised outreach.
- **Agency:** Build bespoke prospecting and enrichment systems per client; this is increasingly a paid service line in itself.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [clay.com](http://clay.com) (£124+/mo Starter; serious tier from £349+/mo).
2. Build a *Table* — import a source, add enrichment columns, add AI columns.
3. Use *Claygent* for per-row AI research.
4. Push enriched, scored leads to Apollo, HubSpot, Salesforce or Smartlead.$md$, '2017 by Kareem Amin and Varun Anand (New York).', 'https://clay.com'),
  ('apify', 'Apify', 'automation', 7, 10, 'Apify is a web scraping and browser automation platform built around the concept of "Actors" — pre-built scrapers for every major site you''d realistically want data from (Instagram, LinkedIn, Google Maps, Amazon, Trustpilot, Reddit, TikTok, Shopify…', $md$Apify is a web scraping and browser automation platform built around the concept of "Actors" — pre-built scrapers for every major site you'd realistically want data from (Instagram, LinkedIn, Google Maps, Amazon, Trustpilot, Reddit, TikTok, Shopify, [Booking.com](http://Booking.com)), plus a full SDK and managed cloud infrastructure for writing your own custom scrapers in JavaScript or Python. The output is structured JSON or CSV that pipes cleanly into LLMs, Sheets, warehouses, Notion, Make, n8n or Zapier — making Apify the data layer underneath much of the modern AI marketing stack. It's the tool that turns "I wish I had every competitor's prices, reviews and ad creative weekly" from a hypothetical into a working scheduled job. Apify is also unusually generous on free credits, which means you can build a small competitive-intelligence pipeline before paying anything. Founded in Prague in 2015.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Scrape every competitor's Instagram engagement metrics, Trustpilot reviews and Shopify product feeds weekly; pipe into a Notion dashboard.
- **Calo:** Pull restaurant / dark-kitchen competitor menus, prices and delivery times across UK / GCC at a regional level for ongoing pricing intelligence.
- **Agency:** Productise "market intelligence as a service" for clients — Apify scrapes, Clay enriches, Claude synthesises, Notion reports it. Recurring revenue.
**Getting started**
1. Sign up at [apify.com](http://apify.com).
2. Browse the *Apify Store* for a pre-built Actor matching your need.
3. Run on demand, schedule, or trigger from Make / n8n / Zapier.
4. Pipe the JSON / CSV output into your warehouse, Notion, or Sheets.$md$, '2015 by Jan Čurn and Jakub Balada (Prague).', 'https://apify.com'),
  ('vs-code', 'Visual Studio Code', 'coding-development', 8, 1, 'Visual Studio Code is the industry-standard code editor — a free, open-source application from Microsoft that has become the default editor for the majority of professional software developers worldwide, and the editor that virtually every freelance engineer, contractor or…', $md$Visual Studio Code is the industry-standard code editor — a free, open-source application from Microsoft that has become the default editor for the majority of professional software developers worldwide, and the editor that virtually every freelance engineer, contractor or agency dev will already have installed. Its strength is the combination of being lightweight (faster than full IDEs), genuinely open-source (so it works for any language and any stack), and surrounded by an enormous extension ecosystem that lets you bolt on anything you need: GitHub Copilot for AI completions, the Claude Code or Continue extensions for full agentic AI assistance, language servers for every major language, debuggers, Git tooling, design tooling and more. For a marketing or ops team, VS Code is the right base when you want a free, well-known editor that everyone can hand a project off to without retraining — and you can layer Cursor or AI extensions on top wherever a person actually wants them.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** Use VS Code + GitHub Copilot to maintain the Shopify Liquid theme — the editor every freelance dev will already be using.
- **Calo:** Use VS Code as the team's standard editor across regional dev contractors; it's free, well-known, and ensures handoffs work everywhere.
- **Agency:** Standardise on VS Code so every project is portable across freelancers; layer Claude / Cursor on top for senior engineers who want it.
**Getting started**
1. Download from [code.visualstudio.com](http://code.visualstudio.com).
2. Install extensions: GitHub Copilot, Continue (open-source AI assistant), Claude Code (see next).
3. Set up workspace settings per project.
4. Use the integrated terminal + Source Control panel — most marketers will never need anything else.$md$, 'Microsoft, released April 2015. Open source.', 'https://code.visualstudio.com'),
  ('claude-code', 'Claude Code', 'coding-development', 8, 2, 'Claude Code is Anthropic''s terminal-based agentic coding tool — install it once with `npm`, run `claude` in any directory, and Claude becomes an autonomous engineer working alongside you in the terminal.', $md$Claude Code is Anthropic's terminal-based agentic coding tool — install it once with `npm`, run `claude` in any directory, and Claude becomes an autonomous engineer working alongside you in the terminal. It reads the codebase, asks clarifying questions, plans the work, edits files, runs commands, runs tests, debugs failures, and ultimately ships features and opens pull requests, all from inside a chat-style interface. The reason it has become the most-loved AI coding tool among senior engineers in 2026 isn't autocomplete speed — it's reasoning depth and taste: Claude Code is unusually good at understanding what you actually want, breaking large tasks into a sensible plan, refusing to make plausible-but-wrong shortcuts, and maintaining context across long, multi-step work. For non-engineers, it works as a "deputy engineer" you can hand a goal to ("add an engraving preview component to the product page using the existing design system") and trust to handle the implementation; for senior engineers, it's a force multiplier that handles the implementation while they focus on architecture and review.
**Example applications**
- **D2C jewellery brand:** A non-engineer founder runs `claude` in the Shopify theme repo and asks for a custom "engraving preview" feature — Claude Code reads the codebase, ships the change, runs the build, and opens a PR.
- **Calo:** Wire Claude Code into the Crystal Ball forecasting tool — a senior engineer hands Claude Code the GitHub repo + spec, and it implements the next forecasting module with tests, while the engineer reviews PRs.
- **Agency:** Pair every developer with Claude Code as a force multiplier — the agency ships landing pages, tracking pixels and Shopify customisations 3–5× faster, with the senior engineer in the loop on architecture only.
**Getting started**
1. Install via the terminal: `npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code` (Node.js required).
2. Run `claude` in any directory — log in with an Anthropic account.
3. Ask in plain English: "add an engraving preview component to the product page using the existing design system".
4. For long, multi-step work, kick off a *plan*, let it execute, then review changes via Git — Claude Code is built to behave like a real engineer collaborator, not just an autocomplete.
5. Combine with Cursor or VS Code for the moments where you want a GUI editor; both happily coexist.$md$, 'Anthropic, 2021. Claude Code launched 2024 / 2025 as the agentic CLI sibling of Claude.', 'https://www.anthropic.com/claude-code'),
  ('awesome-claude-plugins', 'awesome-claude-plugins', 'coding-development', 8, 3, 'A community-maintained, automatically-updated ranked list of the top \~100 most-adopted Claude Code plugin repositories on GitHub, scored by stars, subscribers and plugin count.', $md$A community-maintained, automatically-updated ranked list of the top \~100 most-adopted Claude Code plugin repositories on GitHub, scored by stars, subscribers and plugin count. Browsing it is the fastest way to see what real teams are actually installing rather than what's just being talked about — at the top of the list you'll find Anthropic's official plugins (claude-plugins-official, knowledge-work-plugins for Cowork), Anthropic's first-party skills repo, multi-agent orchestration suites (claude-flow, oh-my-claudecode, agents), memory systems (claude-mem, claude-supermemory, beads), Chrome DevTools MCP, Playwright skills, safety nets that intercept destructive commands, and per-stack plugins for Postgres, Vue, Expo, AWS, Firebase, Supabase and Stripe. The list is regenerated continuously via n8n workflows scanning GitHub for adoption signals.
**How to use it**
1. Open the README — the table is ranked by adoption (stars × subs × plugin count).
2. Pick a plugin matching your need (e.g. `compound-engineering-plugin`, `claude-mem`, `chrome-devtools-mcp`, `claude-code-safety-net`).
3. Install it in Claude Code or Cowork via `/plugin install <repo>` or follow each repo's specific instructions.
4. For curated bundles, look at *anthropics/claude-plugins-official* (Anthropic's own marketplace) and *EveryInc/every-marketplace* (Every's curated set).$md$, null, 'https://github.com/quemsah/awesome-claude-plugins'),
  ('skills-sh', 'skills.sh', 'coding-development', 8, 4, 'The Agent Skills Directory — a public leaderboard and registry of every open-source skill, ranked by installs, with a single-command install via `npx skills add <owner/repo>`.', $md$The Agent Skills Directory — a public leaderboard and registry of every open-source skill, ranked by installs, with a single-command install via `npx skills add <owner/repo>`. The top entries reveal where the ecosystem is investing: Vercel Labs' React and design-system skills, Anthropic's first-party document and design suite (frontend-design, pdf, pptx, xlsx, docx, mcp-builder, brand-guidelines), Microsoft's Azure skills, the *superpowers* engineering methodology, *impeccable* design-polish skills, *marketingskills* covering CRO/SEO/copy/ads, and a long tail covering Obsidian, n8n, Supabase, Firebase, Expo, Stripe and dozens of other stacks. [Skills.sh](http://Skills.sh) works across Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, Gemini, Copilot, Cline, Windsurf, Goose, Trae, Roo, Kilo and almost every modern AI agent — install once, use everywhere.
**How to use it**
1. Browse the leaderboard at [skills.sh](http://skills.sh); filter by category, search by name, or sort by Trending / Hot.
2. Note a skill you want — e.g. `anthropics/skills/pptx` or `coreyhaines31/marketingskills/seo-audit`.
3. Install with one command in your project root: `npx skills add anthropics/skills` (adds a whole bundle) or pick individual skills.
4. The skill is now available to whichever agent you're running — Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, etc.
For a marketing-led operator like Calo, the most relevant collections to start with:
